==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Halse
<hw>Halse</hw> <pr>(h⟦add⟧ls)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>healsian</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To embrace about the neck;
to salute; to greet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each other kissed glad⟦br⟧
And lovely <qex>halst</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To adjure; to beseech; to entreat.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O dere child, I <qex>halse</qex> thee,⟦br⟧
In virtue of the Holy Trinity.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halse</ent>⟦br⟧

